# Commit Message Template for Semantic Versioning
# 
# Use one of these formats:
#
# feat: add new feature (MINOR version bump: 2.6.0 ? 2.7.0)
# fix: fix a bug (PATCH version bump: 2.6.0 ? 2.6.1)
# feat!: breaking change (MAJOR version bump: 2.6.0 ? 3.0.0)
# chore: maintenance task (no version bump)
# docs: documentation only (no version bump)
# style: code style change (no version bump)
# refactor: code refactoring (no version bump)
# perf: performance improvement (PATCH version bump)
# test: add tests (no version bump)
#
# Examples:
#
# feat: add match duplication feature
#
# fix: resolve QR code scanning crash
# 
# Fixes issue where QR codes with special characters 
# would cause the scanner to fail
#
# feat!: redesign storage system
#
# BREAKING CHANGE: Old match data format is incompatible.
# Users must export and re-import their matches.
#
# More info: https://www.conventionalcommits.org/
